{
  "texts": [
    "The multifaceted and contentious nature of CSR and corporate tax avoidance means that a single country, researcher, or institution cannot comprehensively address the research problem.",
    "As a result, much of the existing literature in this domain has emerged from partnerships involving various countries, researchers, and organisations.",
    "Analysis the co-authorship network analysis conducted using VOSViewer identified the most influential countries in terms of the number of citations and total link strength.",
    "As shown in Table 2, the United Kingdom emerged as the country with the highest number of citations at 1,854, followed by India (1,715), the United States (1, 424), and China (1, 421).",
    "This indicates the substantial impact and recognition of research originating from these countries."
  ]
}